parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Premature Steer Tire Wear and Misalignment
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Premature wear on steer tires can lead to reduced traction, increased stopping distances, and increased risk of tire blowouts, which can cause accidents. Misalignment can also cause uneven tire wear, reduced fuel efficiency, and compromised vehicle handling.
symptoms: annual replacement of steer tires required.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Front Axle and Steering System Issues
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Problems with the front axle and steering system can cause vibration, uneven tire wear, and compromised vehicle handling, which can increase the risk of accidents.
Failure of the shock absorbers can cause reduced vehicle stability, compromised handling, and increased stopping distances, which can increase the risk of accidents.

The failure of the wiring harness can cause electrical system malfunctions, leading to issues with various vehicle components, such as lights, doors, and computer systems, which can compromise vehicle safety and performance.
The frequent need for clutch adjustment can lead to difficulty shifting transmission, which can cause accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
clutch pedal sticks to the floor
clutch pedal does not return to its normal position.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Transmission problems related to the air ride system can cause loss of vehicle control, leading to accidents or other safety hazards.
symptoms: unusual noises or vibrations from the transmission.
